KS_SmartRename - Unity Editor Bulk Rename Tool
===============================================

What is this?
-------------
KS_SmartRename is a Unity Editor utility for bulk renaming assets and
GameObjects using a chainable operation stack. It provides a live two-column
preview before any changes are applied, works on Project window and Hierarchy
selections simultaneously, and uses Unity's AssetDatabase API so all GUID
references and serialized connections are preserved after rename.

The tool was created to replace the workflow of renaming assets outside of
Unity with PowerRename or similar tools, which breaks asset references and
causes Addressables address mismatches that require manual correction.

KS_SmartRename performs the following operations:

- Renames assets using AssetDatabase.RenameAsset (preserves GUIDs and all
  serialized references)
- Renames GameObjects using Undo.RecordObject (fully undoable via Ctrl+Z)
- Renames folders using AssetDatabase.RenameAsset
- Chains multiple rename operations in order: Search/Replace, Add Prefix,
  Add Suffix, and Number, each applied to the output of the previous
- Builds a live two-column preview (Original / Renamed) before applying,
  with changed characters highlighted in blue and unchanged characters in green
- Detects name collisions within the batch and flags them as errors before
  any rename is attempted
- Filters the preview list by asset type (.anim, .prefab, .mat, etc.),
  GameObject, or Folder
- Optionally syncs the Addressables address string when renaming a registered
  asset (reflection-based, no project settings change required)
- Warns before applying asset renames since they cannot be undone via Ctrl+Z
- Applies silently for GameObject-only batches since those are fully undoable
- Tooltips on every control, including a regex reference table and whole-word
  explanation on the relevant toggles


How do I use it?
----------------

Setup
-----

1. Place KS_SmartRename.cs anywhere inside your Unity project's Assets folder.
   An Editor subfolder is recommended but not required. The #if UNITY_EDITOR
   guard at the top of the file ensures it never compiles into a build
   regardless of where it is placed.

2. Open the tool from the Unity menu bar:

      Tools > KS > Smart Rename

   Or right-click any selection:

      Project window  -- right-click > KS Smart Rename
      Hierarchy       -- right-click > KS Smart Rename

3. Select the assets or GameObjects you want to rename. The preview list
   updates immediately to reflect the current selection. You can change
   the selection while the window is open and it will update.


Operations
----------

The tool uses a stack of operations applied in order from top to bottom.
Each operation receives the output of the one above it.

The window opens with a single Search/Replace operation by default.

Adding operations:

   Click any of the + buttons in the Operations header row to add a new
   operation of that type to the bottom of the stack:

      + Search/Replace  -- find and replace a substring
      + Prefix          -- prepend text to the name
      + Suffix          -- append text to the name
      + Number          -- append or prepend a sequential number

Each operation card has:

   - A toggle on the left to enable or disable it without removing it
   - Arrow buttons (▲ ▼) to reorder it in the stack
   - An X button to remove it

Click Reset to clear the entire stack and start with a single fresh
Search/Replace operation.


Search / Replace
----------------

1. Enter the text to find in the Search for field.

2. Enter the replacement text in the Replace with field. Leave blank to
   delete the matched text.

3. Toggle any combination of the following options:

   Regex
   -----
   Treats the Search for field as a regular expression pattern instead of
   plain text. Any regex error is shown inline below the fields.

   Common patterns (hover the Regex toggle in the tool for a quick reference):

      ^        Start of name      ^MTX_ matches only if name begins with MTX_
      $        End of name        _L$ matches only if name ends with _L
      .        Any character      M.ge matches Mage, Moge, M_ge
      *        Zero or more       Lo* matches L, Lo, Loo
      +        One or more        Lo+ matches Lo, Loo but not L
      [abc]    Any of these       [LR] matches L or R
      [0-9]    Range              matches any digit
      (a|b)    Either a or b      (Mage|Warrior) matches either word
      \d       Any digit          \d+ matches one or more digits

   Case sensitive
   --------------
   When on, the search must match the exact capitalisation.
   Off by default. Example: searching for 'mage' with Case Sensitive ON
   will not match 'Mage'.

   Whole word
   ----------
   Only matches the search term when it appears as a complete word, not
   as part of a longer word. Word boundaries include underscores, digits,
   and the start or end of the name.

   Example with search term 'Arm':
      MTX_Arm_L     -- matches   (Arm is bounded by underscores)
      MTX_ForeArm_L -- no match  (Arm is part of ForeArm)

4. The preview updates live as you type.


Add Prefix
----------

Enter the text to prepend to every item name. Applied after any
Search/Replace operations above it in the stack.


Add Suffix
----------

Enter the text to append to every item name. Applied after any operations
above it in the stack.


Number
------

Appends or prepends a sequential number to each item name.

   - Position (Append / Prepend)
                       -- whether the number goes at the end or the start
   - Sep               -- separator between the name and the number
                          (default underscore). Can be left empty.
   - Start             -- the first number in the sequence (default 1)
   - Step              -- how much the number increments per item (default 1)
   - Padding           -- minimum digit width, zero-padded.
                          Padding 2 produces 01, 02 ... 10, 11.
                          Padding 3 produces 001, 002 ... 010, 011.

Numbers are assigned in the order items appear in the master list, which
is the order they appeared in your selection. The active type filter does
not affect numbering order.


Type Filter Bar
---------------

When the selection contains more than one type of item, a filter bar appears
below the Options row. Click any filter to narrow the preview list to that
type only:

   All     -- show everything (default)
   .anim   -- show only animation clip assets
   .prefab -- show only prefab assets
   GO      -- show only GameObjects
   Folder  -- show only folders
   etc.

The filter only affects which items are visible and selectable in the preview.
It does not affect numbering order or items outside the filtered view.


Preview List
------------

The preview list shows all items in the current selection (or the filtered
subset) with the following columns:

   Checkbox  -- include or exclude this item from the Apply operation
   Icon      -- asset type icon or GameObject icon
   Type      -- short type label (anim, prefab, GO, Folder, etc.)
   Original  -- the current name
   Renamed   -- the name that will be applied. Characters that were added
                or changed by the operations are shown in blue with a blue
                background. Characters carried over from the original are
                shown in green. Red text with a warning icon indicates a
                name collision within the batch.

Batch selection buttons:

   Select All    -- check all visible items
   Deselect All  -- uncheck all visible items
   Invert        -- toggle every checkbox
   Changes Only  -- check only items whose name will change

The checkbox in the column header selects or deselects all visible items.

Hover over any control to see a tooltip describing what it does.


Applying
--------

1. Review the Renamed column. No changes have been made yet at this point.

2. Click Apply or press Enter while a text field is focused to apply the
   rename to all checked items that have a valid new name.

3. If any assets are in the batch, a confirmation dialog will appear
   reminding you that asset renames cannot be undone. GameObject-only
   batches apply immediately without a dialog.

4. After applying, the preview refreshes automatically to reflect the
   new names. The operation stack is preserved so you can continue
   working on the updated selection.


Addressables Sync
-----------------

If the Addressables package is present in the project, the Sync Addressables
address checkbox will become active in the Options row. When enabled, renaming
a registered asset also updates its Addressables address string using the same
search/replace logic applied to the filename.

The sync is reflection-based and requires no changes to Scripting Define
Symbols or Project Settings. It detects the package automatically on startup
and logs a confirmation to the Console when found.

If the address does not contain the original asset name, it is left unchanged.


Notes
-----

- Asset renames use AssetDatabase.RenameAsset and cannot be undone via Ctrl+Z.
  The confirmation dialog is shown before any asset rename is applied.
- GameObject renames use Undo.RecordObject and are fully undoable.
- Name collisions within the batch are detected in the preview and blocked
  from applying. Colliding items are highlighted in red.
- Folders are included in the rename list and renamed via AssetDatabase.
- Sub-assets (materials embedded inside FBX files) are not supported for
  renaming and will not appear in the list.
- The operation stack resets to a single Search/Replace on domain reload
  (e.g. after recompiling scripts). It does not persist between sessions.
- The type filter bar only appears when the selection contains more than
  one type of item.
- Hover over any control in the tool to see a tooltip. The Regex and
  Whole Word toggles include extended explanations and examples.


Limitations
-----------

- Asset renames cannot be undone. There is no undo support at the
  AssetDatabase level in Unity.
- Sub-asset renaming is not supported.
- The operation stack does not persist across domain reloads or Unity
  restarts.
- Addressables sync applies the same string replacement to the address
  that was applied to the filename. Addresses with a completely different
  format from the filename will not be updated correctly.
- Duplicate name collision detection is batch-local. It does not check
  whether a name already exists in the destination folder on disk.


Changelog
---------

v1.0
  - Initial release
  - Search/Replace with regex, case-sensitive, and whole-word options
  - Operation stack: Search/Replace, Add Prefix, Add Suffix, Number
  - Live two-column preview with per-item checkboxes
  - Changed characters highlighted in blue, unchanged in green in the
    Renamed column
  - Type filter bar dynamically built from selection
  - Folder support
  - Right-click context menus in Project window and Hierarchy
  - Enter key triggers Apply when a text field is focused
  - Addressables address sync via reflection, no project settings required
  - Asset rename confirmation dialog
  - Batch collision detection
  - Styles rebuilt on domain reload
  - Tooltips on every control, including regex reference table and
    whole-word examples on the relevant toggles


